The TDD exercise is complete. All 9 tests for Conway's Game of Life are passing:

1. Empty grid returns empty grid
2. Single live cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two live cells die (underpopulation)
4. Live cell with 2 neighbors survives
5. Live cell with 3 neighbors survives
6. Live cell with 4+ neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
8. Blinker oscillator transforms correctly
9. Block (2x2) remains unchanged as still life

The implementation in `src/game-of-life.ts` uses a 2D array grid with padding/trimming to handle infinite grid expansion, and follows the four Game of Life rules via named predicates (`survives`, `isReborn`) that directly map to domain vocabulary.
